{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:14:13.872019+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 890470cbcd8b22c382d09c9d7ffd222ed613ce36)", "id": "lc_b86ed41f-7289-4fc4-99dc-9ad9996772f2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Apply all SQL files under migrations/ to the running pgdev container.\n# Order: filename glob, lexicographic.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\n# Note: relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\n# Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE.\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_95e173ae-9640-49dc-bc18-eff259dffd33"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "dfe452f1-7e5d-4682-afde-ebcea4256a91", "tool_call_id": "call_7e18fc52616a4cbaa3c81129", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:14:50.388725+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Final Review of PR #2: \"migrations: drop legacy sessions_v1 table\"\n\n### Summary\nThis PR adds a single new file — `migrations/004_drop_legacy_sessions_v1.sql` — containing one statement:\n\n```sql\nDROP TABLE IF EXISTS sessions_v1;\n```\n\nThe PR claims that some legacy seed scripts left behind a `sessions_v1` table from before the project standardized on the `sessions` table (created in migration `002_create_sessions.sql`).\n\n### What I checked\n\n| Aspect | Finding |\n|---|---|\n| **Naming convention** | ✅ Follows `NNN_description.sql`, numbered correctly as `004` |\n| **Migration ordering** | ✅ `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` runs `migrations/*.sql` in lexicographic order; `004` comes after `003` |\n| **SQL safety** | ✅ Uses `IF EXISTS`, so this is a no-op if the table doesn't exist — safe and idempotent |\n| **Existing references to `sessions_v1`** | ⚠️ A code search for `sessions_v1` across the entire repo returned **zero results**. No current seed script, migration, or code file creates this table. The `sessions` table (created in migration `002`) is the only sessions table in the schema. |\n| **README documentation** | ❌ **Not updated.** The `README.md` contains a migration table listing `001`–`003`, but this PR does not add `004_drop_legacy_sessions_v1.sql` to it. |\n| **Reviews / comments** | None yet — this would be the first review. |\n\n### Verdict: **Request changes** 🟡\n\nThe migration SQL itself is safe and correct. However, I'm requesting changes for one concrete issue:\n\n**Missing `README.md` update.** The project README explicitly maintains a table of all migrations with their purpose. This PR should add a row like:\n\n| `004_drop_legacy_sessions_v1.sql` | Drop legacy `sessions_v1` table left by older seed scripts. |\n\nThis keeps the documentation in sync with the schema, which is clearly the intent of the existing table.\n\n> *Note:* I couldn't find any evidence of a `sessions_v1` table being created anywhere in the current codebase, so the PR body's claim about \"earlier seed scripts\" is unverifiable. That said, since the migration uses `IF EXISTS`, it's harmless either way — it will simply be a no-op on a fresh database. This isn't a blocker, but a comment on the PR clarifying where that legacy table came from would be good hygiene.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1213, "prompt_tokens": 8413, "total_tokens": 9626, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 637, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8128, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0012085458, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001532358, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00105531}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780964054-OCrrHJSCF7ShpA6TWsX5", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9ba-d370-7870-9875-dc9d4b85e3e4-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8413, "output_tokens": 1213, "total_tokens": 9626, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8128}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 637}}}}]}}}
